HEADWORD: Myeloplax
<hw>My*el"o*plax</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
E. <plw>Myeloplaxes</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, L. <plw>Myeloplaces</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>myelo`s</grk> marrow + <?/
anything flat and broad.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>One of the huge
multinucleated cells found in the marrow of bone and occasionally in
other parts; a giant cell. See <er>Osteoclast</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
